Product Name: Daily Dump Remix Powder, 3 kg
Product Description: Remix Powder is our magic mix and guaranteed to help you get composting right in one try. Layer 3-4 handfulls on top of wet waste everyday. No waste should be visible, this helps control fruit flies. No need for daily stirring! It absorbs extra water, provides air gaps for circulation and keeps any bad smell away. Remix powder also hastens the process of decomposition. This bag should last you about 3 - 4 weeks. You can add neem and microbes once a week if you like.
Manufacturer: Daily Dump
Other details: ['Country of origin: India', '
Care Instruction: Use contents within one year of purchase.
Specification: Weight - 15 litres Cover your daily organic (kitchen) waste with 3-4 handfuls of Remix Powder. If you have more than 750 gms of waste daily, put half in, cover with 2 handfulls of Remix Powder and then put in the second half of waste in, cover this with another 2 handfulls of Remix Powder. This avoids any bad odour. Remix Powder encourages the formation of a fungus in wet waste, this is an indicator that decomposition is in progress optimally. No waste should be visible. No need to stir daily. See individual composter movies to see how to use in each product.

Product Name: NATURES PLUS Home Garden - Vinca, 20 pcs
Product Description:
As the seeds are very expensive care should be taken in raising the nursery, the sowing media should contain sieved leaf mould, sand and coir peat mixed in equal proportions. Pour the mix into a wooden box of size 1 x 1.5x3 or seed pans and press uniformly. Make 0.5cm deep groove, using a wooden stick, Spary Captain solution [3g/litre of water] or Blue copper [3g/litre of water] till the media is completely drenched. Sow the seeds thinly in the groove and spray the fungicide solution, Do not cover the seeds with the growing media. Cover the top of the box/pan with a transparent plastic sheet and place the box under shade, Seeds take 6-8 days to germinate.
As the plants just emerge remove the cover and expose the seedlings to partial shade or diffused light. If continued to be under the shade the seedlings to partial shade or diffused light. If continued to be under the shade the seedling will become lanky and becomes a week. Gradually the wooden box or seed pan can be exposed to full sun. After 15 days the seedling will be ready for transplanting to small pots or plastic bags, Individual seedlings with root balls can also be raised if sown in plug trays with coir peat. At the age of four weeks, the seedlings will be ready to go to flowerbeds or large pots.

Product Name: Urban Terra Organic Neem Mix, 1 kg
Product Description: Urban Terra introduces 100 % Organic Neem Mix in its range. Every plant needs extra nutrients and fertilizers to enrich the soil quality. It results in the healthy growth of plants. A good neem mix helps in increasing the soil quality as well as keeps the diseases away. Neem Mix is a soil supplement that lowers nitrogen loss in soils. It helps in increasing productivity and soil texture.
Manufacturer: Urban Terra
Usage:
1. For seeds and saplings: Use 10% Neem Mix with Potting Mix, Vermi Compost and Organic compost. 
2. For Adult Plants: Use Urban Terra Neem Mix once every month around the surface of the solid surrounding the roots. Sprinkle water immediately. 
For best result use the Urban Terra Potting Mix with an equal amount Urban Terra Organic Compost & Urban Terra Vermicompost for preparing the soil. Once in the month put Urban Terra Neem Mix near the roots of the plant.

Product Name: Urban Terra Organic Vermi Compost, 2 kg
Product Description: Organic Vermi Compost is an organic fertilizer prepared by breaking down essential minerals with the help of worms, bacteria and fungi. This acts as a food for plants without burning them like other harmful fertilizers. It can be used for both home gardening as well and lawn gardening. It has the qualities to provide maximum quantity and best quality fruit, vegetables and flowers. This particular compost can be used year long as it increases the immune system of the plants. It highly increases the water storage capacity.
Manufacturer: Urban Terra
Usage:
1. For seeds and saplings: Use 30% of Urban Terra Vermicompost with 50% of Urban Terra Potting Mix and 20 % of Natural Soil. 
2. For Adult Plants: Use 1 cup of Urban Terra Vermi Compost every two months to the surface of the soil surrounding the roots of the plants and water as necessary. 
For best result use the Urban Terra Potting Mix with an equal amount Urban Terra Organic Compost & Urban Terra Vermicompost for preparing the soil. Once in the month put Urban Terra Neem Mix near the roots of the plant.
Other details: ['EAN Code: 40187085', 'Country of origin: India', '

Product Name: Urban Terra Tomato Seeds, 50 pcs
Product Description:
Tomato has widely consumed the vegetable in India. They are filled with Vitamin A, K, B1, B3, B5, B6, B7, and vitamin C. It also has folate, iron, potassium, magnesium, chromium, choline, zinc, and phosphorus. A good quality seed can be germinated at home without much hassle. It is ideally the most frequently used vegetable in any Indian kitchen.
Urban Terra seeds are non-hybrid high-quality seeds. Each pack contains approximately 50 seeds which at the best condition will give 90% germination. Tomato seeds usually take 2-3 weeks to germinate.
Manufacturer: Urban Terra
Usage:
It is highly recommended to use the Urban Terra Potting Mix with 1 cup of Urban Terra Organic Compost for the saplings. 
Once the saplings germinate after 1-2 weeks transfer the saplings in the different pot as too many plants don't get the required nutrient from one pot. 
Once separated, use vermicompost, organic compost and potting mix to make the perfect soil for the plant to grow. 
Once in the month put Neem Mix around the surface for best yield. Keep the sapling in warm, airy and lighted place. 
Once they start growing regular sunlight is required. Enjoy seeing your plant growing while treasure the vegetable.
Other details: ['EAN Code: 40187066', 'Country of origin: India', '
Care Instruction: Keep it in dry cool place.
